    style P fill:#ffccbc,stroke:#bf360c,stroke-width:2px
    style R fill:#ffccbc,stroke:#bf360c,stroke-width:2px
    style T fill:#ffccbc,stroke:#bf360c,stroke-width:2px
```

### 4.2 Diagram: JDBC Object Lifecycle (Detailed Block-Level Architecture)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    APP[Java Application Code] --> LOAD[Step 1: Class.forName Driver]
    LOAD --> REG[DriverManager Registered]
    REG --> CONN[Step 2: getConnection]
    CONN --> CONNOBJ[Connection Object]
    CONNOBJ --> CSTMT[Step 3a: createStatement]
    CONNOBJ --> CPREP[Step 3b: prepareStatement]
    CSTMT --> EXECQ[Step 4: executeQuery SELECT]
    CPREP --> EXECU[Step 4: executeUpdate INSERT UPDATE DELETE]
    EXECQ --> RS[ResultSet]
    EXECU --> AFF[Rows Affected Count]
    RS --> NEXT[Step 5: rs.next Loop]
    NEXT --> PROC[Process Row Data]
    PROC --> CLOSE[Step 6: Close All]
    CLOSE --> END[Program End]
    AFF --> CLOSE
    style APP fill:#bbdefb,stroke:#1565c0
    style CONN fill:#c8e6c9,stroke:#1b5e20
    style RS fill:#fff59d,stroke:#f9a825
    style CLOSE fill:#ef9a9a,stroke:#b71c1c
```

### 4.3 Diagram: Cursor State Machine (Embedded SQL)

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> DECLARED : EXEC SQL DECLARE cursor
    DECLARED --> OPENED : EXEC SQL OPEN cursor
    OPENED --> FETCHING : EXEC SQL FETCH INTO host_vars
    FETCHING --> OPENED : More rows available
    FETCHING --> FETCHED_ALL : SQLCODE = 100
    FETCHED_ALL --> CLOSED : EXEC SQL CLOSE cursor
    CLOSED --> [*]
    FETCHING --> ERROR : SQLCODE < 0
    ERROR --> CLOSED : EXEC SQL CLOSE cursor
    CLOSED --> [*]
```

