#### **Model Solution to Question A(b):**

```java
import java.sql.*;

public class StudentApp {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String url  = "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/university_db";
        String user = "root";
        String pass = "password";

        Connection        conn   = null;
        PreparedStatement pstmt  = null;
        ResultSet         rs     = null;

        try {
            /* (i) INSERT a new row using PreparedStatement */
            Class.forName("com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver");
            conn = DriverManager.getConnection(url, user, pass);

            String insertSQL = "INSERT INTO Student(sid, sname, marks) VALUES (?, ?, ?)";
            pstmt = conn.prepareStatement(insertSQL);

            pstmt.setInt(1, 201);
            pstmt.setString(2, "Ananya");
            pstmt.setFloat(3, 78.5f);

            int inserted = pstmt.executeUpdate();
            System.out.println("Rows inserted: " + inserted);
            pstmt.close();

            /* (ii) SELECT rows where marks > 60 using ResultSet */
            String selectSQL = "SELECT sid, sname, marks FROM Student WHERE marks > ?";
            pstmt = conn.prepareStatement(selectSQL);
            pstmt.setFloat(1, 60.0f);

            rs = pstmt.executeQuery();

            System.out.println("\nStudents with marks > 60:");
            System.out.println("SID\tNAME\tMARKS");
            while (rs.next()) {
                int    sid   = rs.getInt("sid");
                String sname = rs.getString("sname");
                float  marks = rs.getFloat("marks");
                System.out.println(sid + "\t" + sname + "\t" + marks);
            }

        } catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
            System.out.println("Driver not found: " + e.getMessage());
        } catch (SQLException e) {
            System.out.println("SQL Error Code: " + e.getErrorCode());
            System.out.println("SQL Error Message: " + e.getMessage());
        } finally {
            /* Close in reverse order: ResultSet ŌåÆ Statement ŌåÆ Connection */
            try { if (rs    != null) rs.close();    } catch (SQLException e) { }
            try { if (pstmt != null) pstmt.close(); } catch (SQLException e) { }
            try { if (conn  != null) conn.close();  } catch (SQLException e) { }
        }
    }
}
```

**Explanation for marks:**

- `Class.forName(...)` ŌĆö Loads the JDBC driver class. **(0.5 mark)**
- `DriverManager.getConnection(...)` ŌĆö Establishes a connection; the URL follows the `jdbc:subprotocol:subname` format. **(1 mark)**
- `prepareStatement(...)` ŌĆö Precompiles the SQL, allowing safe parameter binding via `?` placeholders, which prevents SQL injection. **(1 mark)**
- `pstmt.setInt(1, 201)` ŌĆö The first `?` is bound to 201. The index is **1-based**, a common student error. **(1 mark)**
- `executeUpdate()` ŌĆö Used for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE; returns the row count. **(0.5 mark)**
- `executeQuery()` ŌĆö Used for SELECT; returns a `ResultSet`. **(0.5 mark)**
- `rs.next()` ŌĆö Cursor advance; returns `false` at end of data. **(1 mark)**
- `finally` block ŌĆö Guarantees resource cleanup, even on exception. **(1 mark)**
- Closing order ŌĆö ResultSet ŌåÆ Statement ŌåÆ Connection (LIFO). **(0.5 mark)**

